<h1>Gregory Brown</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://practicingdeveloper.com/now/">practicingdeveloper.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
New Haven
CT
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Independent software developer, writer, and teacher
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help programmers explore the kinds of questions that make their work more meaningful.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I am generally unhappy with the state of the tech education world.  I want to encourage software developers to adopt a more human-centric focus.  The more skilled someone is, the more opportunity they'll have to make better choices in life.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Not all hard work is created equal. If you have a sense of purpose, you can work like crazy and be left wanting to do more. Without that, it's nothing but a grind.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“Thinking, Fast and Slow”
</p>

